The paper focuses on utilizing ConvNets for action recognition, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new layer and pooling strategies to improve the performance, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves encoding local descriptors, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
